		<header level = "0">Overpenetration and Missed Shots</header>
<box>
<text>Overpenetration and Missed Shots  On a base level, Ops and Tactics ignores the aftereffects of using improper ammunition when in combat, or when one misses their shot. This variant rule adds the notion of missing or shooting through your target.</text>
</box>
		<text>   If an attack roll results in a missed attack by a ranged weapon,continues on for 5 range increments in the direction it was fired until it loses momentum force and lands on the ground or collides with another object.</text>
		<text>   If an object or target is within the line of fire of thecollides with that target, but the target is considered flat-footed, as they are unaware that the attack is even coming for them. If the roll succeeds, then it is considered a hit and damage is rolled as it would be if it were a normal attack.</text>
		<text>   The hardness of an object also effects if it can be penetrated.stop the round at all, and the round passes through. Treat that object as concealment, not cover.</text>
		<header level = "1">Overpenetrating a target</header>
		<text>   If the ammunition does half or more more of the total possiblethough the target and has the possibility to hit someone else. This only happens with the following kinds of ammunition:</text>
